Instructions: Start in a plank position, lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor, then push back up.
Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, lower your body by bending your knees, then return to standing.
Grab a pull-up bar with palms facing away, pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar, then lower yourself down.
Step forward with one leg, lower your hips until both knees are bent at 90 degrees, then push back to starting position.
Stand with feet hip-width apart, grip the barbell, lift by extending your hips and knees, then lower it back.
Lie on a bench, grip the barbell, lower it to your chest, then press it back up.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand, curl your arms upward while keeping your elbows stationary, then lower back down.
Hold dumbbells at shoulder height, press them overhead until arms are fully extended, then lower back down.
Position yourself on parallel bars, lower your body by bending elbows, then push back up.
Stand with feet flat, raise your heels until standing on toes, then lower back down.
